reviews.text:
Disclaimer: I love pork but I only eat imported pork because local pork comes with a foul smell and taste that I found disgusting.

I ordered their original soup and unfortunately the soup and pork shoulder/belly had the said disgusting foul smell and taste. No idea what kind of pork this establishment uses but from my personal experience it's definitely not Japanese/American/Canadian/Danish/Spanish pork.

Those who are immuned to local pork taste are welcomed to ignore my opinion.
Easy good place . Atmosphere is pleasant I try Butao ramen taste great not too heavy ,price is also good if I’m in the aria would definitely try some other flavor .

Good Ramen, nice and filling but something missing to add that extra star in terms of flavour. Great selection and options I would advise to Try it, enjoy it but don't expect to be wowed only thing. Hope for just something more.
Delicious ramen. Tried the red king and green king

The ramen from Butao is just average, but restaurant decoration is good.
The noodle of restaurant is actually nice, but the taste of their broth(赤王) just average and not that great.  
Other than the food, the shop actually is comfortable.  Tables here are not too packed, so it left you some privacy between tables.  Although they have a glass wall by the busy street, but it't noisy inside the shop.
Just as other restaurant in the area, they will clean up your table fast, and get ready for next customers, so here is not a place for chat

reviews.text: One of the new high rise building consisting of upmarket restaurants.

I had only one drink there, so I can't say much about the food but the view is pretty good and the staff was super friendly. They even made some discount on the occasion of my b-day and offered some shots. I thinks its definitely worth trying, at least, once)
When i asked the concierge where the washroom is , they said there is no washroom in the whole plaza... this is so weird
Great location near Times Square and with a number of eateries, including good Japanese ones like Ootoya.
Is a brand-new landmark in Causeway Bay, surrounded by top restaurants and top fitness centres, highly recommended!!

reviews.text:
豫園 (銅鑼灣)
銅鑼灣登龍街18號 V Point 26樓

招牌松子鮮魚最開胃，可以加碗白飯送汁!

今天本來是去吃火鍋的，不過朋友病了轉了中餐。朋友本來電話去訂位說沒有位不能預訂，但之後我們walk in就有位。這家餐廳是全層分左面廳，右面廳。左面廳全部沒有景，右面廳裝修非常華麗。如果真的要去吃就要訂有景的一邊。

食物方面，我覚得整體ok, 我特別喜歡招牌松子魚，酸酸甜甜一整條，好味。脆皮素鴨也很出色。

如果想食高力豆沙或豆沙鍋餅就要預早叫定好樣廚房準備。那天我們大約10:30pm叫這兩款甜品，全都沒有！
One of the new high rise building consisting of upmarket restaurants.
餐飲為主，但宣傳唔多，下面又冇餐牌可以睇
貴價又難食的高檔菜式

I had only one drink there, so I can't say much about the food but the view is pretty good and the staff was super friendly. They even made some discount on the occasion of my b-day and offered some shots. I thinks its definitely worth trying, at least, once)
